Slaughter! There is no greater glorification of Khaine, the God of Murder, and no more popular form of worship amongst the Dark Elves. It is through killing that Dark Elves rise above other beings. Once engulfed in enough bloodshed, they will often feel their murderous prowess increase, as if Khaine himself was guiding the blades of his disciples.
Dark figures move and twist within the mists surrounding this unit, providing additional protection against the foe.
A fell horn is sounded, frightening the charging enemy and leaving them vulnerable to a counter charge.
This spiky armor both protects the wearer and makes it difficult to strike them without also getting poked by its poisoned barbs.
This units exudes a befuddling aura. Orders are misheard, vision is blurred, minds are muddied, and any hope of organization is extinguished.
This units excels in aquatic environment, fighting with ease in waters most would struggle to even walk through.
With a triumphant roar this unit charges into the fray, inspring all around them.

The art of hitting an enemy where they are weakest is perhaps the most important skill of any tactician.
The light has never been extinguished and never will, such is the power that keeps it alight. For those ranged against the light, it is blinding, and so hampers their attacks considerably.
Invigorated by battle, lusting for blood, their fury only grows as the fight goes on.
It is one thing to train against the horrors of the Old World, another to have faced them and come back alive.
Battle is an art in Cathay. Like all things it requires a delicate balance that takes years of training to master.
This filthy, pulsating blister rapidly grows before suddenly bursting, showering the enemy with its disgusting fluid and all the maladies contained within.
The greatest gift bestowed by the Urfather upon His faithful is the promise of being reborn anew through hideous, pestilent death.
A fire is set within the very rock itself, causing the ground to splinter and the raging lifeblood of the world to gush forth and consume the enemy.
A hail of magical energy is unleashed, transmuting foes into unliving golden statues.
A spray of sizzling silver slivers rain from the sky to impale the caster's enemy.
The Winds of Magic swirl violently around this unit.
A cackling, flaming visage appears before the Wizard. With a gleeful screech, it swirls around the battlefield, immolating anything in its way.
Focusing all his mystical might, the Pyromancer strikes the foe with a flurry of incandescent missiles.
The Wizard ensorcels allied weapons, making them burn with a savage fire. The targets of the spell are augmented with superior flaming blades.
The caster weaves a confounding fog that numbs and deludes enemies, causing them to stumble and stagger.
The tender lies of Slaanesh are silenced, and any blessings bestowed by the Dark Prince vanish as fear once more takes hold of a once impetuous heart.
Some warriors care not for their own personal safety, and so work themselves into a whirlwind of destruction and mindless violence!
Devouring the heart of a bull Rhinox or Mournfang, raw vitality is projected into the Great Maw, increasing the ferocity of the Ogres' attacks.
After downing the toxic and utterly repulsive innards of a Troll, the Ogres' wounds seem to stitch themselves together before their enemies' dumbfounded eyes.
By consuming a hunk of tooth-breaking granite, the spellcaster bestows the rock's resilience and the sturdiness of the mountains themselves into his brethren.
Stuffing a handful of bones into his mouth, the spellcaster crunches them up whilst cursing his foes, who are crushed by a giant fist which pounds them to dust.
Choking, scalding, blinding, superheated ash streams across the battlefield whenever this nasty little spell is cast.
Scratching biting gnashing gnawing... A swarm of filthy rats skitters in this unit's wake.
Force feeding beasts Kvas sends them into a frenzy.

Storm clouds roil above this unit, and those unlucky enough to get too close are soon struck by spiteful bolts.

At one with the frozen plains and snowy tundra, wherever this one goes, they bring the icy heart of the Motherland with them.
Such is the volume of snowfall that enemies must wade through that the air itself becomes a near-opaque wall of ice no gaze can penetrate.
This eldritch explosion propels lacerating shards of ice outwards, devastating anyone caught in its deadly squall.
A mighty, freezing gale slashes at the enemy with icy shards.
Snow and ice rise from the land, freezing and blinding any and all in their path with an unnatural cold.
A deluge of lacerating, fist-sized shards of ice falls from the sky, battering the foe into submission.
